verses.text_plain: Be merciful unto me, O God: for man would swallow me up; he fighting daily oppresseth me.
verses.verse_html:
1Be merciful unto me, O God: for man would swallow me up; he fighting daily oppresseth me. ▼
▼ Michtam…: or, A golden Psalm of David

footnotes.body_text: ▼ Michtam…: or, A golden Psalm of David
footnotes.body_html: ▼ Michtam…: or, A golden Psalm of David

verses.text_plain: Mine enemies would daily swallow me up: for they be many that fight against me, O thou most High.
verses.verse_html:
2Mine enemies would daily swallow me up: for they be many that fight against me, O thou most High. ▼
▼ enemies: Heb. observers

tokens.text: against me, O thou most High

verses.text_plain: What time I am afraid, I will trust in thee.
verses.verse_html: 3What time I am afraid, I will trust in thee.

verses.text_plain: In God I will praise his word, in God I have put my trust; I will not fear what flesh can do unto me.
verses.verse_html: 4In God I will praise his word, in God I have put my trust; I will not fear what flesh can do unto me.

verses.text_plain: Every day they wrest my words: all their thoughts are against me for evil.
verses.verse_html: 5Every day they wrest my words: all their thoughts are against me for evil.

verses.text_plain: They gather themselves together, they hide themselves, they mark my steps, when they wait for my soul.
verses.verse_html: 6They gather themselves together, they hide themselves, they mark my steps, when they wait for my soul.

verses.text_plain: Shall they escape by iniquity? in thine anger cast down the people, O God.
verses.verse_html: 7Shall they escape by iniquity? in thine anger cast down the people, O God.

verses.text_plain: Thou tellest my wanderings: put thou my tears into thy bottle: are they not in thy book?
verses.verse_html: 8Thou tellest my wanderings: put thou my tears into thy bottle: are they not in thy book?

verses.text_plain: When I cry unto thee, then shall mine enemies turn back: this I know; for God is for me.
verses.verse_html: 9When I cry unto thee, then shall mine enemies turn back: this I know; for God is for me.

verses.text_plain: In God will I praise his word: in the Lord will I praise his word.
verses.verse_html: 10In God will I praise his word: in the Lord will I praise his word.

verses.text_plain: In God have I put my trust: I will not be afraid what man can do unto me.
verses.verse_html: 11In God have I put my trust: I will not be afraid what man can do unto me.

verses.text_plain: Thy vows are upon me, O God: I will render praises unto thee.
verses.verse_html: 12Thy vows are upon me, O God: I will render praises unto thee.

verses.text_plain: For thou hast delivered my soul from death: wilt not thou deliver my feet from falling, that I may walk before God in the light of the living?
verses.verse_html: 13For thou hast delivered my soul from death: wilt not thou deliver my feet from falling, that I may walk before God in the light of the living?
